               <person><!--donor-->
                  <persName corresp="PRS0000">Additio 2 mentiones ras Sǝbḥat  (ras Sǝbḥat ʾArägawi, b. ca. 1844, d. 1914), with baptismal name Kidanä Maryam, as the donor. The names of his relatives are also mentioned: his mother Wälättä Śǝllase, his wife Wälättä Maryam, his children Gäbrä Ḥǝywät, Wäldä Gäbrǝʾel, ʾArʾaya Śǝllase.&#xD;
Names of other individuals are written in some supplication formulas: Gäbrä Śǝllase (esp. fols. 6ra l.10, 136ra l.17, 150rc l.32) and Wäldä Maryam (fols. 24rb ls.9-10, 91rb l.31, 144vb ls.6-7). In two supplication formulas “people of the place” (säbʾa hagär) (esp. fol. 29vb) and as the “people of the place, children of the community” (säbʾa hagär däqiqä maḫbär) are mentioned (esp. fol. 153rc).</persName>
